Hey, 
If you assume deep web = overlay network, then Zeronet is a deep web (like Bittorrent, I2P, Tor, RetroShare, whatever). 
A darknet is a network where you don't connect to unknown peers.
Freenet, Retroshare and some other can be used as darknets but Zeronet can't.

I personally think that there is no deep web. Why a part of the web would be more deeper than an other? It is mostly a word for people who don't really understand what is the web and what are theses network.
